@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title StreamDesk - Creating and Managing a Kanban Task (Dynamic View)

actor User
participant "Browser\n(React App)" as Browser
participant "TanStack Query\n(Client Cache)" as Query
participant "Express API\n(Routes)" as API
participant "Auth Middleware" as Auth
participant "Zod Validator" as Validator
participant "Database Layer\n(Drizzle ORM)" as DB
participant "PostgreSQL" as Postgres
participant "WebSocket Server" as WS
participant "Other Connected\nClients" as Others

== Task Creation Flow ==

User -> Browser: Click "Create Task"\non Kanban Board
activate Browser

Browser -> Query: mutate('/api/kanban/cards',\n{title, description, listId})
activate Query

note right of Query
  Optimistic update:
  UI shows new task immediately
  before server response
end note

Query -> API: POST /api/kanban/cards
activate API

API -> Auth: Check session
activate Auth
Auth --> API: Session valid ✓
deactivate Auth

API -> Validator: Validate request body
activate Validator
Validator --> API: Valid ✓
deactivate Validator

API -> DB: insertTask(taskData)
activate DB

DB -> Postgres: INSERT INTO kanban_cards
activate Postgres
Postgres --> DB: Return inserted task
deactivate Postgres

DB --> API: Return created task\n(with id, timestamps)
deactivate DB

API --> Query: 201 Created\n{task object}
deactivate API

Query --> Browser: Update cache\nwith new task
deactivate Query

Browser --> User: Show task in UI
deactivate Browser

== Real-time Synchronization ==

note over WS
  WebSocket polls database
  every 10 seconds
end note

WS -> DB: getKanbanCards()
activate DB
DB -> Postgres: SELECT * FROM kanban_cards
activate Postgres
Postgres --> DB: Return all cards
deactivate Postgres
DB --> WS: Return updated cards
deactivate DB

WS -> Others: Broadcast 'tasks_update'\n{cards: [...]}
activate Others
Others -> Others: Update local cache\nand re-render UI
deactivate Others

== Error Handling Scenario ==

User -> Browser: Try to create task\nwith invalid data
activate Browser

Browser -> Query: mutate('/api/kanban/cards',\n{title: ""})
activate Query

Query -> API: POST /api/kanban/cards
activate API

API -> Validator: Validate request body
activate Validator
Validator --> API: Validation failed ✗\n"Title is required"
deactivate Validator

API --> Query: 400 Bad Request\n{error: "Title is required"}
deactivate API

Query --> Browser: Show error toast
deactivate Query

Browser --> User: Display validation error
deactivate Browser

== WebSocket Disconnection Handling ==

note over WS
  If WebSocket disconnects,
  system falls back to
  REST API polling
end note

WS -> WS: Connection lost
WS -> WS: Attempt reconnect\n(exponential backoff)

Others -> API: Fallback: GET /api/kanban/cards\n(every 30 seconds)
activate API
API -> DB: getKanbanCards()
activate DB
DB --> API: Return cards
deactivate DB
API --> Others: Return current state
deactivate API

@enduml

